::: el-h1
# [![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,){.svg-icon .right-triangle}]{.heading-collapse-indicator .collapse-indicator .collapse-icon}***Adventurers\' Guild:*** **Leaders:** Edward & Abigale Teach (Green) {#_**Adventurers'_Guild**_**Leaders**_Edward_&_Abigale_Teach_(Green)_0 .heading heading="_**Adventurers' Guild:**_ **Leaders:** Edward & Abigale Teach (Green)" dir="auto"}
:::

::: el-p
The Adventurers\' Guild is the largest group in
[Avalon](2.-locations/avalon/avalon-(between-astra-&-terra).html){.internal-link
tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Avalon (Between Astra & Terra)"
data-href="Avalon (Between Astra & Terra)" target="_self"
rel="noopener nofollow"} by population. The other factions mostly scout
their members from particularly promising or accomplished members of
this guild. It is also the only faction with an [**established presence
outside the Avalon Archipelago**.]{.mark} They make their goal
maintaining peace in remote parts of the world, where neither city
guards nor most armies want to go. Preserving the life of the people and
adventurers is their priority, but it\'s not always an easy endeavour.
[Edward](.html){.internal-link data-href="Edward" target="_self"
rel="noopener nofollow"} &
[Abigale](images/abigail-teach.png){.internal-link
tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Abigail Teach.png"
data-href="Abigail Teach.png" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow"}
are the ever traveling duo at the helm of the Adventurers\' Guild.
They\'re the most popular leaders among Avalon\'s top brass due to their
frequent travels and public appearances. They\'ve been on so many
adventures throughout the years that telling whether a story about their
exploits is truth or myth has become almost impossible to tell.

# [![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,){.svg-icon .right-triangle}]{.heading-collapse-indicator .collapse-indicator .collapse-icon}Relics {#Relics_0 .heading heading="Relics" dir="auto"}
:::

::: el-p
Names carry power. The more well known a name the more power it has.
Relics are powerful items often associated with figures of legend and
derive their power from the respect their names demand. Weapons like
Excalibur, Durendal and Ascalon are among the most well known Relics out
there. The few capable of wielding them often have their names and
stories forever engraved in the annals of history. Certain Relics have
lost their names. They often hold power capable of toppling nations on
their own and are sealed away in the most dangerous parts of the world.
These Forgotten Relics are a priority for many major factions as getting
hold of even one can completely shift the balance of power in this
world.
